org.apache.river.test.spec.servicediscovery

Class DiscardWaitOverrideProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.river.test.spec.servicediscovery.DiscardWaitOverrideProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, OverrideProvider

    public class DiscardWaitOverrideProvider
extends Object
implements OverrideProvider
    A test override provider which searches the test properties for a non-zero value of org.apache.river.sdm.discardWait. If found, an override is generated for net.jini.lookup.ServiceDiscoveryManager.discardWait having that value. An override is only generated for tests (serviceName == null)

      • getOverrides

        public String[] getOverrides(QAConfig config,
                             String serviceName,
                             int count)
                      throws TestException
        Description copied from interface: OverrideProvider
        Provide the overrides to pass when obtaining a Configuration from a configuration provider. The serviceName and instance count are passed when the override is to apply to a service; for a test override, serviceName must be null and the instance count is ignored. The overrides are provided as pairs in the returned string array. The first element of the pair is the fully qualified entry name, and the second is the entry value. The '=' character is omitted.
        Specified by:
        getOverrides in interface OverrideProvider
        Parameters:
        config - the test config object
        serviceName - the service name, or null for a test override
        count - the instance count for the service
        Returns:
        the array of override strings, which must not be null, but may be of length 0
        Throws:
        TestException - if a fatal error occurs
